			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001042_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 63003 top right--><!--typescript cutting in left hand corner need to see original to transcribe-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Barnet.</p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> June 1857</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Daubeny</persName></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>It will give 
<lb/>me much pleasure 
<lb/>to accept of the 
<lb/>Honorary degree 
<lb/>from the ancient 
<lb/>University of 
<lb/>Oxford of which 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001042_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>you have kindly 
<lb/>given me notice 
<lb/>I hope no great 
<lb/>speechifying is 
<lb/>expected on the 
<lb/>occasion. My 
<lb/>latinity would 
<lb/>now take the 
<lb/>form of Sichuana 
<lb/>if I tried that 
<lb/>language</p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001042_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Will you be kind 
<lb/>enough to inform 
<lb/>me what is 
<lb/>expected of me?</p>
<lb/><p>I shall be happy 
<lb/>to dine with the 
<lb/><persName>Provost of 
<lb/>University College</persName>
<lb/>according to his 
<lb/>invitation on 
<lb/>the 23<hi rend="sup">d</hi></p>

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001042_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I am Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>Most truly yours</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>Prof. Daubeny</persName></p>

	<pb n="0005" facs="liv_001042_0005"/><!--pb/@n='5'--> 
<!-- Hand 02 all of page 5-->
<lb/><p><hi rend="underline"><!--in top left hand corner--></hi></p>
<lb/><p>17/6/1857</p>
<lb/><p>A.L.S.</p>
<lb/><p><hi rend="underline">David Livingstone <!-- double underline--></hi></p>
<lb/><p>Explorer<!--layout???--></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">1857.</p>
<lb/><p>Accepting the <choice><abbr>Hon</abbr><expan>Honorary</expan></choice> Degree of Oxford 
<lb/>University <!-- long line--></p>
<lb/><p><unclear cert="medium">Fine</unclear> letter.</p>
<lb/><p>"hopes no great speechifying on this 
<lb/>occasion</p>
<lb/><p><hi rend="underline">Portrait</hi></p>
<lb/><p><del type="strikethrough" resp="#CO"><!-- wavy strikethrough???--> Enclosed slip for Album by Robert Moffat 
<lb/>Livingstone's father-in-law <!--how to do hyphens in text??--></del></p>
			
